The '''Institute for Environment and Sustainability''' (IES) used to be a specialised institute of the [[Joint Research Centre]] directorate of the [[European Commission]], based in [[Ispra]], [[Italy]]. Its mission was to provide scientific and technical support to EU policies for the protection of the [[Natural environment|environment]] contributing to [[sustainable development]] in Europe.
The [[Joint Research Centre]] underwent a reorganization in 2016, where the work of the scientific institutes was redistributed among scientific Directorates. ==External links== *[https://ec.europa.eu/jrc/en Joint Research Centre] *[http://ec.europa.eu/index_en.htm European Commission] {{coord missing|Italy}}
